### Feature 6: Guardrails for Restricting Query Scope

Restrict queries to only answer from uploaded document content. Block off-topic, harmful, or out-of-scope questions.

#### [NEW] [guardrails.py](file:///b:/GenAI_Project/core/guardrails.py)

```python
# Three-layer guardrail system:
#
# Layer 1: TOPIC FILTER — Check if query is related to uploaded documents
#   - Embed the query, check cosine similarity against document embeddings
#   - If max similarity < threshold (0.2), reject as off-topic
#
# Layer 2: CONTENT SAFETY — Block harmful/inappropriate queries
#   - Keyword blocklist for harmful content categories
#   - Pattern matching for injection attempts ("ignore previous instructions")
#
# Layer 3: SCOPE ENFORCEMENT — Prevent the LLM from answering beyond docs
#   - Enhanced system prompt that strictly limits to document context
#   - Post-generation check: flag responses that say "based on my knowledge"
#
# Returns: (is_allowed, rejection_reason)
```

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///b:/GenAI_Project/app.py)
- Add guardrail check before `handle_query()`:
  ```python
  guardrail = Guardrail(system["embeddings"], system["vs_manager"])
  is_allowed, reason = guardrail.check(query)
  if not is_allowed:
      add_message("assistant", f"🛡️ {reason}")
  ```

#### [MODIFY] [rag_chain.py](file:///b:/GenAI_Project/core/rag_chain.py)
- Strengthen `RAG_SYSTEM_PROMPT` to reinforce scope restrictions
- Add post-generation guardrail check

#### [MODIFY] [sidebar.py](file:///b:/GenAI_Project/ui/sidebar.py)
- Add toggle: `st.toggle("🛡️ Guardrails", value=True)` in RAG Settings section
- When disabled, skip guardrail checks (power-user mode)

